      • HIGH_WATER_MARK

        public static final int HIGH_WATER_MARK
        Allows a Channel to change the internal UPA output queue depth water mark, which has a default value of 6,144 bytes. When the UPA output queue exceeds this number of bytes, the write method internally attempts to flush content to the network. Value is an int. Default is 6144.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SYSTEM_READ_BUFFERS

        public static final int SYSTEM_READ_BUFFERS
        Allows a Channel to change the TCP receive buffer size associated with the connection. Value is an int. Default is 64K.
        Please note that if the value is larger than 64K, the value needs to be specified before the socket is connected to the remote peer.
        • For servers and SYSTEM_READ_BUFFERS larger than 64K, use BindOptions.sysRecvBufSize(int) to set the receive buffer size, prior to calling Transport.bind(BindOptions, Error).
        • For clients and SYSTEM_READ_BUFFERS larger than 64K, use ConnectOptions.sysRecvBufSize(int) to set the receive buffer size, prior to calling Transport.connect(ConnectOptions, Error).
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SYSTEM_WRITE_BUFFERS

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PRIORITY_FLUSH_ORDER

        public static final int PRIORITY_FLUSH_ORDER
        Allows a Channel to change its priorityFlushStrategy. Value is a String, where each entry in the String is either:

        • H for high priority
        • M for medium priority
        • L for low priority

        The String should not exceed 32 entries. At least one H and one M must be present, however no L is required. If no low priority flushing is specified, the low priority queue will only be flushed when no other data is available for output. Default is "HMHLHM".

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
